@page "/Play"

<MudText Typo="Typo.h3" Align="Align.Center">How to connect to the game</MudText>
<MudDivider Class="mt-5 mb-5"></MudDivider>
<MudGrid>
    <MudItem xs="12" lg="4">
        <MudPaper Style="margin: auto;">
            <MudText Typo="Typo.h5" Class="pa-2">Step 1: Download A Client</MudText>
            <MudDivider Class="mb-2"></MudDivider>
            <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Align="Align.Center" Class="pa-4">
                In order to connect to & play the game, you will need to download a client that allows you to connect
                to Telnet sockets. There are many of these clients available, both to download & on the web. We also
                plan
                to add our own to the website. But, in the interim I can suggest a popular, free client: <MudLink
                    Href="https://www.mudlet.org/download/" Target="new">Mudlet</MudLink>
            </MudText>
        </MudPaper>
    </MudItem>
    <MudItem xs="12" lg="4">
        <MudPaper Style="margin: auto;">
            <MudText Typo="Typo.h5" Class="pa-2">Step 2: Enter connection info</MudText>
            <MudDivider Class="mb-2"></MudDivider>
            <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Align="Align.Center" Class="pa-4">
                Adding new connection info will vary depending on the client that you chose. In mudlet, click "new
                profile" and add the following info:
                <MudText Typo="Typo.subtitle1" Color="Color.Success">
                    play.exodusmud.com
                </MudText>
                <MudText Typo="Typo.subtitle1" Color="Color.Success">
                    PORT 9000
                </MudText>
            </MudText>
        </MudPaper>
    </MudItem>
    <MudItem xs="12" lg="4">
        <MudPaper Style="margin: auto;">
            <MudText Typo="Typo.h5" Class="pa-2">Step 3: Enjoy!</MudText>
            <MudDivider Class="mb-2"></MudDivider>
            <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Align="Align.Center" Class="pa-4">
                You're in! If you're new to MUDs or have more questions, feel free
                to stop into the Exodus Mud Discord or ask for help on any public channel!
                <MudDivider Class="mb-2 mt-2"></MudDivider>
                <MudLink Href="https://discord.gg/h6NZDdU8">Discord</MudLink>
            </MudText>

        </MudPaper>
    </MudItem>
</MudGrid>
